{"campground":{"facility_id":"232593","parent_asset_id":"444","inventory_type_id":"3","facility_type":"STANDARD","order_components":{"camping_equipment":true,"group_leader_address":true,"group_leader_details":true,"group_size":true,"num_vehicles":true,"pass":true},"facility_lookups":null,"facility_description_map":{"Facilities":"\u003cp\u003eThis year-round campground offers 142 sites with electric hookups. Sites 1-75 are newly renovated sites and have concrete pads and sewer. Amenities include flush toilets, showers, drinking water and dump stations. A picnic shelter is provided for parties and family functions.\u003c/p\u003e","Natural Features":"The campground is situated on Catoma Creek in a forest of hickory and pine. The region offers a mild climate for year-round camping.","Overview":"Gunter Hill Campground offers a peaceful scene of trees and nature on the backwaters of the Alabama River. \n\u003cbr/\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\nThe fishing is excellent, providing challenges for the master angler as well as the occasional cane pole fisherman. Boating, hunting and hiking are popular activities.","Recreation":"The area's waterways offer excellent fishing for crappie, bass and catfish. A boat ramp is provided for easy river access.\n\u003cbr/\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\nThe Lowndes Wildlife Management area, located nearby, covers 12,500 acres and offers prime hunting for whitetail deer, wild turkeys and hogs, and a variety of small game and waterfowl.\n\u003cbr/\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\nThe campground provides a basketball court and playground, offering additional recreation opportunities for visitors."},"facility_name":"GUNTER HILL","city":"","state":"","facility_adaaccess":"N","facility_directions":"From I-65, take exit 167 onto US-80 west. Continue for 9 miles, then turn right on County Road 7 and follow signs into the campground.","facility_email":"","facility_email_display":false,"facility_map_url":"","facility_latitude":32.3666667,"facility_longitude":-86.4666667,"facilit